      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I need some help with a formal email. I'm an HR manager at a logistics company and I have to write a disciplinary email to an employee. They've been about 15 minutes late to their shifts every day for the last two weeks. Can you draft something professional and firm but not like, super aggressive? We want to keep it strictly business.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Subject: Urgent: Addressing Attendance Concerns\n\nDear [Employee's Name],\n\nI hope this message finds you well. I am writing to address a matter of concern regarding your attendance at work. Over the past two weeks, it has come to our attention that you have been arriving approximately 15 minutes late to your shifts on several occasions. As an HR manager, I must emphasize the importance of punctuality in maintaining the efficiency and smooth operation of our logistics company.\n\nIn the spirit of fostering a supportive and professional work environment, we would like to discuss this matter further. We understand that unforeseen circumstances may arise, and we are open to hearing any explanations you may have. However, consistent tardiness is impacting not only your colleagues but also the overall productivity of our team.\n\nWe kindly request that you adhere to your scheduled start times and strive to arrive on time for your shifts moving forward. We value your contributions to our company and believe that with a little more punctuality, you can continue to be an integral part of our team.\n\nPlease let us know if there are any underlying issues that we can assist with to help you improve your punctuality. We are here to support you and are confident that we can work together to resolve this matter.\n\nThank",
